WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:05.797
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:05.880 --> 00:06.881
<i>kids:</i>
<i>Pig!</i>

00:06.965 --> 00:10.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:10.176 --> 00:10.552
<i>Goat!</i>

00:10.635 --> 00:13.471
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:13.555 --> 00:14.806
<i>Banana!</i>

00:14.889 --> 00:19.477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:19.561 --> 00:20.770
<i>Cricket!</i>

00:20.854 --> 00:27.152
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:33.533 --> 00:35.160
- A-a-a-achoo!

00:35.243 --> 00:38.413
<i>all:</i>
<i>Pig! Goat! Banana! Cricket!</i>

00:41.541 --> 00:44.502
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:44.586 --> 00:45.211
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:45.295 --> 00:48.631
<i>[strings intensify]</i>

00:48.715 --> 00:50.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:50.800 --> 00:52.635
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:52.719 --> 00:56.598
<i>- This is a door,</i>
<i>and this is a window...</i>

00:56.681 --> 00:58.600
[glass shatters]

00:58.683 --> 01:02.187
<i>But mostly, this is a door.</i>

01:02.270 --> 01:03.772
<i>Open this door, and--</i>

01:03.855 --> 01:06.357
oh, boy, that was really spinny.

01:06.441 --> 01:08.818
[vomits and belches]

01:08.902 --> 01:11.321
Sorry.
Inside this door

01:11.404 --> 01:13.323
is a world of imagination--
of wonder--

01:13.406 --> 01:17.952
of super cool stuff, like--
scary eyeball?

01:18.036 --> 01:19.913
<i>Blink, blink.</i>

01:19.996 --> 01:24.000
<i>It is also where a pig,</i>
<i>a goat, and a banana...</i>

01:24.083 --> 01:26.669
- Me too!
I'm a cricket!

01:26.753 --> 01:28.671
- Will learn to be careful
what they wish

01:28.755 --> 01:30.882
when they enter...
[bongo flourish]

01:30.965 --> 01:33.468
The Goofy Turkey Zone!

01:33.551 --> 01:34.677
[glass shatters]

01:34.761 --> 01:35.929
[screams]
all: Cricket!

01:36.012 --> 01:37.305
- [humming]
-<i> Submitted for your approval--</i>

01:37.388 --> 01:40.850
<i>a simple bug</i>
<i>with the simplest of wishes--</i>

01:40.934 --> 01:42.018
<i>Love.</i>

01:42.101 --> 01:43.478
What would he do for love,

01:43.561 --> 01:45.313
and how many times
would this loser--

01:45.396 --> 01:47.023
- Hey! Did you just
call me a loser?

01:47.106 --> 01:51.861
- Yes.
- Why are you even here?

01:51.945 --> 01:52.612
- [screams]

01:52.695 --> 01:55.198
- [humming]

01:55.281 --> 01:56.658
[light buzzes]

01:56.741 --> 02:00.370
Behold, all the things I need
for a perfect date.

02:00.453 --> 02:01.663
- [speaking gibberish]

02:01.746 --> 02:04.165
- Five gallons
of industrial cologne...

02:04.249 --> 02:05.542
[sighs]

02:05.625 --> 02:09.086
And special flowers
I genetically engineered myself.

02:09.169 --> 02:10.922
Part daisy, part orchid.

02:11.005 --> 02:12.715
I call 'em dorkids!

02:12.799 --> 02:14.050
[all snickering]

02:14.133 --> 02:16.386
- [speaking gibberish]
- Whoa.

02:16.469 --> 02:17.929
That's where you're wrong.

02:18.012 --> 02:20.723
{\an3}I'm gonna take Goat out
on a perfect date.

02:20.807 --> 02:23.226
Then she'll see
how amazing I am.

02:23.309 --> 02:26.521
Don't wait up, Burgerstein.
[laughs]

02:26.604 --> 02:27.272
- [speaking gibberish]

02:27.355 --> 02:28.231
- [strumming and humming]

02:28.314 --> 02:30.817
- Goat, would you
look at the clock?

02:30.900 --> 02:33.236
I do believe it's flower time!

02:33.319 --> 02:35.238
[all snickering]

02:35.321 --> 02:37.240
- I'm allergic to dorkids!

02:37.323 --> 02:38.741
{\an3}[sneezes]

02:38.825 --> 02:40.159
{\an1}[crash]

02:40.243 --> 02:40.869
[light buzzes]

02:40.952 --> 02:42.912
- [speaking gibberish]

02:42.996 --> 02:44.914
- No, it was not perfect!

02:44.998 --> 02:46.749
That was my only chance.

02:46.833 --> 02:49.002
Oh, if only I could go back
and do it again,

02:49.085 --> 02:51.337
I'd fix everything I did wrong.

02:51.421 --> 02:54.007
- [speaking gibberish]
- Sure, Burgerstein,

02:54.090 --> 02:56.092
{\an3}I'll just magically
go back in time, and--

02:56.175 --> 03:00.096
[gasps] Whoo! I can go back
in time with my Time-Button!

03:00.179 --> 03:01.723
Ooh! There it is!

03:01.806 --> 03:05.476
I'll travel back in time,
and ask Goat out again.

03:05.560 --> 03:07.645
Go-go, Time-Button!

03:07.729 --> 03:10.940
[bell tolling]

03:11.024 --> 03:12.442
{\an3}[strumming]

03:12.525 --> 03:15.820
{\an1}- Goat, the only thing sweeter
than you is...

03:15.904 --> 03:18.948
Chocolate you!

03:19.032 --> 03:20.825
- Whoa!
Ahh!

03:20.909 --> 03:22.035
{\an1}- Eh...

03:22.118 --> 03:25.955
{\an1}So that's no dorkids
and no giant chocolate Goat.

03:26.039 --> 03:28.166
Let's try it again.

03:28.249 --> 03:30.877
[bell tolling]

03:30.960 --> 03:31.961
Hey, um, Goat,

03:32.045 --> 03:34.422
{\an1}would you like to,
you know,

03:34.505 --> 03:37.300
{\an1}get some nice
non-life threatening ice cream?

03:37.383 --> 03:39.636
- Ice cream? Yum.

03:39.719 --> 03:41.471
- [gasps] Yes!
I--

03:41.554 --> 03:44.015
I mean, cool, cool, whatevs.

03:44.098 --> 03:46.017
<i>[smooth jazz music]</i>

03:46.100 --> 03:48.603
{\an1}Two cones--
any flavor the lady wants.

03:48.686 --> 03:50.813
{\an1}- Oh, thanks.
Um, how 'bout some chocolate?

03:50.897 --> 03:51.731
- Oh! Chocolate!

03:51.814 --> 03:55.193
My, uh--[sighs]

03:55.276 --> 03:57.987
My favorite!

03:58.071 --> 03:59.364
{\an3}- Heh.

03:59.447 --> 04:02.325
- Two scoops of chocolate.
Enjoy.

04:02.408 --> 04:05.036
- Has anyone, like,
seen my pet weasels?

04:05.119 --> 04:08.873
- Huh?
- [grunts]

04:08.957 --> 04:10.959
- [chittering]
- Ah!

04:11.042 --> 04:14.754
- Cricket!
- Time-Button pressy now-now!

04:14.837 --> 04:16.714
[bell tolling]

04:16.798 --> 04:19.300
- Ice cream? Yum.

04:19.384 --> 04:20.843
<i>♪</i> ♪

04:20.927 --> 04:22.428
Um, how 'bout some choc--
- [gibbers]

04:22.512 --> 04:25.682
{\an1}Strawberry!
We'll take the strawberry.

04:25.765 --> 04:28.267
{\an1}Heh.

04:28.351 --> 04:30.687
- [grunting]

04:30.770 --> 04:34.607
My scoop's stuck.
Really got to pull.

04:34.691 --> 04:37.402
[grunting]

04:37.485 --> 04:39.487
- [wheezes]

04:39.570 --> 04:41.239
- [grunting]
[yelps]

04:41.322 --> 04:42.448
- Oh, no-no! Oh, no!
- [screams]

04:44.742 --> 04:46.286
Blah.

04:46.369 --> 04:49.080
Cricket!
- Uh--just a--

04:49.163 --> 04:51.749
oh, please, Time-Button,
don't fail me now!

04:51.833 --> 04:53.042
[bell tolling]

04:53.126 --> 04:55.253
<i>- Well, uh, Cricket?</i>

04:55.336 --> 04:57.005
{\an3}You gonna order
some time this year?

04:57.088 --> 04:58.214
- We're waiting!

04:58.298 --> 04:59.424
{\an3}- Come on,
you're taking all day!

04:59.507 --> 05:00.466
- I have a family!
- [whimpers]

05:00.550 --> 05:03.761
Oh, all I wanted
was the perfect date.

05:03.845 --> 05:05.054
- Come on, buddy.

05:05.138 --> 05:07.765
It's not like the planet's
going to explode

05:07.849 --> 05:09.851
if you pick the wrong flavor.

05:09.934 --> 05:12.562
[all laughing]

05:12.645 --> 05:15.106
- [gulps]
Okay, um...

05:15.189 --> 05:17.817
Rum Raisin?
Ye?

05:18.860 --> 05:22.155
- Cricket!

05:22.238 --> 05:24.949
[bell tolling]

05:25.033 --> 05:28.453
- [sighs]
Yep, this date is perfect.

05:28.536 --> 05:29.912
- [speaking gibberish]

05:29.996 --> 05:31.664
{\an1}- Yeah, it'd be nice
if Goat were here,

05:31.748 --> 05:34.625
but how 'bout this Rocky Road?

05:34.709 --> 05:36.169
[dorkids snickering]

05:36.252 --> 05:37.754
all: Goat!

05:37.837 --> 05:41.174
- Goat thinks she can get fame
and fortune for a song

05:41.257 --> 05:43.760
in The Goofy Toofy Zone!

05:43.843 --> 05:47.055
{\an3}- Brrr, I got a wicked
draft in here.

05:47.138 --> 05:48.973
[grunts]
- [yelping]

05:49.057 --> 05:51.434
- ♪ You're such
a cuddly sweetie ♪

05:51.517 --> 05:54.103
♪ I got you
this treasure bag of meaty ♪

05:54.187 --> 05:55.104
♪ Uh, bleaty ♪

05:55.188 --> 05:57.106
I am writing awful songs today.

05:57.190 --> 05:59.233
I need some inspiration.

05:59.317 --> 06:02.111
What do we got?
"How To Quit"?

06:02.195 --> 06:03.613
[blows raspberries]
No.

06:03.696 --> 06:05.615
"Why Bother? For Dum-Dums."

06:05.698 --> 06:08.785
[blows raspberries]
No.

06:08.868 --> 06:11.287
Hey.
"Book of Gorf?"

06:11.370 --> 06:13.331
Huh?
Whoa!

06:13.414 --> 06:15.833
[gasps]
A shrimpy weirdo.

06:15.917 --> 06:18.336
- I am not a weirdo.
I'm Gorf.

06:18.419 --> 06:20.755
You opened the book
and set me free,

06:20.838 --> 06:23.257
so I now I shall
grant you a wish!

06:23.341 --> 06:25.384
Anything your heart desires!

06:25.468 --> 06:27.261
{\an3}- What?
What's the catch?

06:27.345 --> 06:28.137
- There's no catch.

06:28.221 --> 06:30.348
Promise, zero catches.

06:30.431 --> 06:32.100
{\an1}Gorf my heart,
and hope to Gorf.

06:32.183 --> 06:33.976
{\an3}- Okay, well,
you did Gorf your heart,

06:34.060 --> 06:38.314
{\an3}so I wish I was
the greatest musician ever!

06:38.397 --> 06:41.067
- Now, that I can Gorf!

06:41.150 --> 06:43.402
<i>[enchanting music]</i>

06:43.486 --> 06:45.279
- Heh? Wait, a kazoo?

06:45.363 --> 06:47.073
- Gorf's work is done.

06:47.156 --> 06:49.992
Gorf you later!

06:50.076 --> 06:51.494
- No, Burgerstein,

06:51.577 --> 06:54.372
I had a wonderful time with you.

06:54.455 --> 06:55.373
- [speaking gibberish]

06:55.456 --> 06:56.499
{\an1}- Ah!
[glass shatters]

06:56.582 --> 06:57.500
- Hey, Cricket,

06:57.583 --> 07:00.461
{\an3}check out
my new kazoo.

07:00.545 --> 07:02.672
[kazoo plays]

07:02.755 --> 07:05.967
- [sighs]
- [grunts]

07:06.050 --> 07:08.177
♪ ♪

07:08.261 --> 07:12.014
- Wow, that's the greatest
kazoo song I've ever heard.

07:12.098 --> 07:13.516
- [laughs] Isn't it?

07:13.599 --> 07:15.101
Kazoo-a-doodle-doo!

07:15.184 --> 07:17.895
- Burgerstein,
wasn't that just incredi--

07:17.979 --> 07:19.856
[screams]
Burgerstein!

07:19.939 --> 07:21.941
There are bats eating your head!

07:22.024 --> 07:24.443
Ah! Now they're attacking me!

07:24.527 --> 07:26.237
Ow! Why?

07:26.320 --> 07:29.282
Why is this happening?

07:29.365 --> 07:32.160
{\an1}- Banana!
Check-ey this-ey out-ey.

07:32.243 --> 07:36.205
{\an3}- Is that one of them zookies?
'Cause I'll pass.

07:36.289 --> 07:39.959
♪ ♪

07:40.042 --> 07:44.130
{\an3}- It's like sweet candy cake
for my ear mouths.

07:44.213 --> 07:46.382
Goat, you're stupendous.

07:46.465 --> 07:49.886
- Aren't I?
Kazoodles!

07:49.969 --> 07:50.887
♪ ♪

07:50.970 --> 07:54.182
- I could listen to
that kazoo all--

07:55.808 --> 07:57.602
- Wha-ha-ho!
Phew!

07:57.685 --> 07:59.228
Banana,
did you just hear Goat play

07:59.312 --> 08:02.857
her amazing kazoo playing?

08:02.940 --> 08:05.443
- Yeah, then I got blimped.

08:05.526 --> 08:07.278
- Every time
she plays that kazoo,

08:07.361 --> 08:09.071
something horrible happens.

08:09.155 --> 08:11.157
We have to stop Goat!
Come on!

08:11.240 --> 08:12.408
- [groans]

08:12.491 --> 08:16.495
♪ ♪

08:16.579 --> 08:18.581
- Lovin' that kazoo, Goat.

08:18.664 --> 08:19.248
{\an1}[screams]

08:19.332 --> 08:21.792
- Kazoo it up, girl!

08:21.876 --> 08:23.085
[cats yowl]
[screams]

08:23.169 --> 08:25.588
- You should play
a sold-out concert,

08:25.671 --> 08:28.216
so everyone can hear you.

08:29.675 --> 08:32.595
- A big concert,
so everyone can hear me!

08:32.678 --> 08:33.471
But how am I gonna do that?

08:33.554 --> 08:36.724
{\an3}- You! Lady...
[clucking]

08:36.807 --> 08:39.559
{\an3}What was that beautiful music
you were playing?

08:39.644 --> 08:41.354
- Oh, what? This?

08:41.437 --> 08:44.941
{\an8}♪ ♪

08:45.024 --> 08:47.568
{\an8}- Hmm...
I just stepped in a bear trap,

08:47.652 --> 08:49.737
and it really hurts.
[clucks]

08:49.820 --> 08:51.697
I'm Louis Cluck,
big-time record producer,

08:51.781 --> 08:54.784
and I want you to play
a massive concert

08:54.867 --> 08:57.203
and get famous.
- That is so great,

08:57.286 --> 08:59.121
{\an1}but maybe we should take you
to a doctor first.

08:59.205 --> 09:00.122
- No time.

09:00.206 --> 09:01.332
This concert starts
in five minutes.

09:01.415 --> 09:04.085
Play me some kazoo while we go.

09:04.168 --> 09:05.711
♪ ♪

09:05.795 --> 09:07.713
Oh! That's another bear trap.

09:07.797 --> 09:09.674
- [groans]

09:09.757 --> 09:11.842
Oh! That's messed up, son.

09:11.926 --> 09:13.803
[crowd chanting]
Kazoo Goat! Kazoo Goat!

09:13.886 --> 09:15.304
- They're waiting for you, Goat.

09:15.388 --> 09:17.515
You're gonna be a star.

09:17.598 --> 09:19.558
[crowd chanting]
Kazoo Goat! Kazoo Goat!

09:19.642 --> 09:22.645
Kazoo Goat! Kazoo Goat!

09:22.728 --> 09:26.315
- Oh, I have dreamed of this
for so long.

09:26.399 --> 09:27.817
<i>[foreboding music]</i>
Whoa!

09:27.900 --> 09:31.070
Hey! What's the big idea
holding up my show?

09:31.153 --> 09:32.822
- Your kazoo is cursed!

09:32.905 --> 09:34.907
It totally blimped my head.

09:34.991 --> 09:36.826
- Oh, that's just crazy talk.

09:36.909 --> 09:38.786
{\an1}- Yeah, her music
is gonna make us rich,

09:38.869 --> 09:42.164
{\an1}and then after we're rich,
we can look into the bear traps.

09:42.248 --> 09:43.958
Oh, this really hurts.

09:44.041 --> 09:46.294
- Look at him!
Your kazoo did that.

09:46.377 --> 09:47.420
Play it.
You'll see.

09:47.503 --> 09:50.589
{\an1}- [stammers]
I'm not listening.

09:50.673 --> 09:53.009
♪ ♪

09:53.092 --> 09:54.176
- See?

09:54.260 --> 09:56.095
Nothing happ--
- [screams]

09:56.178 --> 09:57.930
- Oh, no!
This kazoo is cursed.

09:58.014 --> 09:59.682
[crowd chanting]
- [groans]

09:59.765 --> 10:01.183
- [grunts]
- Eh?

10:01.267 --> 10:02.518
[chanting]
Kazoo Goat! Kazoo Goat!

10:02.601 --> 10:04.186
- I can't play the concert.

10:04.270 --> 10:07.690
[whimpers] And I was gonna be
the greatest kazoo-er ever.

10:07.773 --> 10:09.525
[sad violin plays]

10:09.608 --> 10:10.526
Gorf! You lousy gnome.

10:10.609 --> 10:13.487
- [laughs]
Did you enjoy my curse,

10:13.571 --> 10:17.491
you sugar-loving turkey kisser?

10:17.575 --> 10:19.827
{\an1}[grunts]

10:19.910 --> 10:23.247
- Not as much as you will.
Kazoo this!

10:23.331 --> 10:24.832
- [laughs]
Ah!

10:24.915 --> 10:25.708
[screaming]

10:25.791 --> 10:27.376
[crowd chanting]
Kazoo Goat!

10:27.460 --> 10:33.841
♪ ♪
[screaming]

10:38.304 --> 10:40.431
Uh-oh.

10:40.514 --> 10:43.017
[screaming]

10:43.100 --> 10:47.229
- Goat got her wish, but then
her wish got Goat's goat.

10:47.313 --> 10:51.233
Wordplay in
The Groovy Duty Zone!

10:52.651 --> 10:53.694
<i>[hard rock flourish]</i>

10:53.778 --> 10:56.489
<i>[eerie music]</i>

10:56.572 --> 10:58.991
<i>- Banana will do anything</i>
<i>to win the local citywide</i>

10:59.075 --> 11:00.409
<i>video game championship,</i>

11:00.493 --> 11:02.703
<i>but when Banana</i>
<i>forgets how to play,</i>

11:02.787 --> 11:06.957
he'll need a helping hand
if he wants to escape...

11:07.041 --> 11:10.086
The Sloppy Jalopy Zone!

11:10.169 --> 11:11.379
[triumphant video game music]

11:11.462 --> 11:14.131
- [laughs]
Man, is that guy annoying.

11:14.215 --> 11:17.093
And man, am I awesome
at video games!

11:17.176 --> 11:18.386
- You're totally gonna win

11:18.469 --> 11:20.971
{\an3}the World Video Game
Championships this year.

11:21.055 --> 11:23.474
- I just have to qualify
on Gut Busters 19.

11:23.557 --> 11:25.351
Of course I already beat
1 through 18,

11:25.434 --> 11:27.311
so hard can that be?
[all cheer]

11:27.395 --> 11:29.814
Thank you! Thank you!

11:29.897 --> 11:34.402
<i>- Bust guts</i>
<i>in 3, 2, 1, bust 'em!</i>

11:34.485 --> 11:35.820
- Jump up--left.

11:38.989 --> 11:40.866
[crowd groans]
Hey!

11:40.950 --> 11:42.076
How did I lose?

11:42.159 --> 11:45.121
Eh, let me try again.

11:45.204 --> 11:46.205
Ah!

11:46.288 --> 11:49.750
[crowd groans]
- Loser!

11:49.834 --> 11:52.711
- How am I ever gonna win
the championships now?

11:52.795 --> 11:56.298
Oh, I'm terrible!
I'm awful!

11:56.382 --> 11:58.217
I've...[sobs]

11:58.300 --> 12:01.303
I've forgotten
how to play video games!

12:01.387 --> 12:04.140
[sobs]

12:04.223 --> 12:05.933
{\an3}- Excuse me,
yellow hot dog man,

12:06.016 --> 12:09.019
but perhaps I can
be of assistance.

12:09.103 --> 12:12.356
{\an1}- Unless you can make me
good at video games, buzz off!

12:12.440 --> 12:14.692
- The name's Dr. Cronenbird,

12:14.775 --> 12:18.571
and I can make you great
at video games.

12:18.654 --> 12:22.741
Now come with me,
you yellow beef machine.

12:22.825 --> 12:25.703
- Uh, okay, I guess.

12:25.786 --> 12:28.747
[lightning crashing]

12:28.831 --> 12:31.792
<i>[eerie music]</i>

12:31.876 --> 12:33.335
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:33.419 --> 12:35.546
{\an1}So how you gonna make me
good at video games again,

12:35.629 --> 12:36.964
Dr. Freak Beak?

12:37.047 --> 12:38.883
- By giving you...

12:38.966 --> 12:41.969
{\an3}the hands of a video game
champion.

12:42.052 --> 12:45.014
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:45.097 --> 12:46.015
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:46.098 --> 12:47.558
- [groans]

12:47.641 --> 12:53.856
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:53.939 --> 12:55.524
[lightning crashing]

12:55.608 --> 13:02.615
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:04.450 --> 13:05.618
- It's done.

13:05.701 --> 13:07.536
{\an3}Long live your
new fresh hands.

13:07.620 --> 13:10.998
- They're amazi--
Ow! Hey!

13:11.081 --> 13:12.875
The hands just hit me?
[groans]

13:12.958 --> 13:14.376
{\an3}- That's just
a slight side effect.

13:14.460 --> 13:16.795
{\an3}It should go away
after a while.

13:16.879 --> 13:18.297
[thunder booms]

13:18.380 --> 13:20.049
[cheers and applause]

13:20.132 --> 13:21.967
- Mary Louise Pizzagut
reporting live

13:22.051 --> 13:24.136
from the World Video Game
Championships where--

13:24.220 --> 13:25.137
[grunts]

13:25.221 --> 13:26.096
- Oh, uh, sorry!

13:26.180 --> 13:27.473
{\an3}New hands.
[chuckles]

13:27.556 --> 13:29.266
Still getting used to 'em.
[chuckles]

13:30.309 --> 13:31.519
{\an8}[knuckles crack]
[grunts]

13:31.602 --> 13:32.561
{\an8}Here goes.

13:32.645 --> 13:35.898
{\an8}Left and a right.
And jump.

13:35.981 --> 13:38.442
{\an8}<i>- Bustin' Guts Bonus achieved!</i>

13:38.526 --> 13:40.945
{\an8}- I'm back, baby!

13:41.028 --> 13:42.154
{\an8}- Banana's unstoppable!

13:42.238 --> 13:45.074
He's bustin' them guts
like a boss!

13:45.157 --> 13:46.450
[all cheering]

13:46.534 --> 13:47.952
<i>[rock music]</i>

13:48.035 --> 13:49.995
- Burn the witch!

13:50.079 --> 13:51.330
- Ahh!

13:51.413 --> 13:53.832
[electronic beeping]

13:53.916 --> 13:55.292
[cheers, electronic chime]

13:55.376 --> 13:59.588
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:59.672 --> 14:00.756
[all groaning]

14:00.839 --> 14:03.342
[warbling tone,
electronic chiming]

14:03.425 --> 14:05.094
- Amazing!
An ugly yellow sausage

14:05.177 --> 14:06.762
has reached the finals.

14:06.845 --> 14:08.514
[cheers and applause]
- [laughs]

14:08.597 --> 14:10.432
Yeah!

14:10.516 --> 14:12.268
[cheers and applause]

14:12.351 --> 14:13.352
Mm.

14:13.435 --> 14:15.312
Look out, world!
- [grunts]

14:15.396 --> 14:16.438
- Hand, knock it off.

14:16.522 --> 14:18.524
Banana is--hey!

14:18.607 --> 14:20.234
Sorry.
Gonna win.

14:20.317 --> 14:21.569
- Oh!
- Oh, sorry.

14:21.652 --> 14:23.529
Um, my hands
are a little rude.

14:23.612 --> 14:26.240
- [grunts]
Those hands aren't rude.

14:26.323 --> 14:27.575
They're mine!

14:27.658 --> 14:30.452
- Robert R. Cade?

14:30.536 --> 14:34.290
The meanest and nastiest
video game champion ever!

14:34.373 --> 14:35.833
- Someone stole my hands,

14:35.916 --> 14:37.751
and I want 'em back!

14:37.835 --> 14:39.878
{\an1}- Uh, all right, here,
take 'em.

14:39.962 --> 14:42.298
- [laughs maniacally]

14:42.381 --> 14:44.550
Now take these noogies!
- [groaning]

14:44.633 --> 14:45.801
{\an8}[grunts]

14:45.884 --> 14:48.262
{\an8}- Now I'm gonna win
this tournament,

14:48.345 --> 14:50.264
{\an8}and everyone here is dumb.

14:50.347 --> 14:53.267
{\an8}[boots stomping]

14:53.350 --> 14:54.977
{\an8}- What am I gonna do?

14:55.060 --> 14:56.770
{\an8}I'm nothing without those hands!

14:56.854 --> 15:00.983
{\an7}- Banana, the power
was never in those hands.

15:01.066 --> 15:02.901
{\an8}It was always
in your heart.

15:02.985 --> 15:05.863
{\an1}Now get out there
and play with your feet!

15:05.946 --> 15:07.114
- [groaning]

15:07.197 --> 15:08.157
- [laughs maniacally]

15:08.240 --> 15:11.076
You can't beat me!

15:11.160 --> 15:13.203
- You're right.
I can't.

15:13.287 --> 15:15.497
But my feet can!

15:15.581 --> 15:17.166
<i>- Three, two, one.</i>

15:17.249 --> 15:19.168
{\an8}<i>B-b-b-b-bust guts!</i>

15:19.251 --> 15:20.628
{\an8}<i>[electronic music]</i>

15:20.711 --> 15:22.838
{\an8}<i>Two guts busted!</i>
[electronic beeping]

15:22.921 --> 15:25.633
{\an9}- Whoa!
Banana's exploding guts!

15:25.716 --> 15:28.344
{\an7}- He's doing more with his feet
in the last 30 seconds

15:28.427 --> 15:30.888
{\an8}than I've done
in a lifetime!

15:30.971 --> 15:33.349
{\an8}<i>- Five guts busted!</i>

15:33.432 --> 15:35.017
{\an8}[electronic beeping]

15:35.100 --> 15:36.226
{\an8}- [grunting]

15:36.310 --> 15:38.187
{\an8}[electronic beeping]

15:38.270 --> 15:40.689
{\an3}- Ah!

15:40.773 --> 15:42.191
Ah! Ah!

15:42.274 --> 15:44.193
My fingers are...

15:44.276 --> 15:46.028
cramping up!

15:46.111 --> 15:47.237
- Letting go
of the controller

15:47.321 --> 15:48.822
is an immediate
disqualification.

15:48.906 --> 15:51.283
Banana is the winner.

15:51.367 --> 15:52.368
{\an8}<i>- [smooching]</i>

15:52.451 --> 15:53.410
{\an8}[electronic chime]

15:53.494 --> 15:55.037
{\an8}- Banana's the winner!

15:55.120 --> 15:57.122
{\an8}[cheers and applause]

15:57.206 --> 15:59.249
{\an8}- Ah!

15:59.333 --> 16:00.709
{\an8}[groans]

16:00.793 --> 16:03.045
- Ha, I did it!
I won!

16:03.128 --> 16:04.838
[all cheering]
Ah!

16:04.922 --> 16:06.256
<i>[sultry saxophone music]</i>

16:06.340 --> 16:07.466
{\an1}- By the way,
are you single?

16:07.549 --> 16:08.467
- [groans]

16:08.550 --> 16:09.635
- [laughs]

16:09.718 --> 16:11.553
Toss me that trophy!

16:11.637 --> 16:13.430
- [grunting]

16:13.514 --> 16:14.390
[trophy zooming]

16:14.473 --> 16:15.724
- Wait, I got no hands!

16:15.808 --> 16:16.725
[trophy clangs]

16:16.809 --> 16:19.311
[groaning]

16:19.395 --> 16:22.481
<i>- To win,</i>
<i>Banana had to lose</i>

16:22.564 --> 16:24.066
<i>what made him a winner.</i>

16:24.149 --> 16:28.070
And when Pig tries to win
over Angry Old Raisin,

16:28.153 --> 16:31.281
he'll learn no good deed
goes unpunished in...

16:31.365 --> 16:34.618
the Hurgle Gurgle
Doctor Squirgle Zone!

16:34.702 --> 16:36.453
[gagging]

16:36.537 --> 16:39.748
{\an1}- Pig, why do you have
that silly look on your face?

16:39.832 --> 16:41.125
- Angry Old Raisin!

16:41.208 --> 16:43.377
{\an3}I just had a little man
talking in my eye.

16:43.460 --> 16:45.254
What are you doing,
fourth best friend

16:45.337 --> 16:46.505
in the whole wide world?

16:46.588 --> 16:48.590
{\an1}- My cockamamy scooter's
out of gas,

16:48.674 --> 16:50.926
{\an1}and I'm gonna be late
for bingo.

16:51.009 --> 16:52.678
{\an3}- Out of gas?
I'll help!

16:52.761 --> 16:54.888
Be right back.
- No, I don't want your hel--

16:54.972 --> 16:57.683
oh, he's already gone.

16:57.766 --> 16:59.059
<i>[hard rock flourish]</i>

16:59.143 --> 17:00.811
[owl hooting]

17:00.894 --> 17:03.397
- A haunted gas station?

17:03.480 --> 17:04.690
<i>[eerie music]</i>

17:04.772 --> 17:08.234
Wow, haunted gas
is so cheap right now.

17:08.318 --> 17:10.487
{\an3}What kind of gas
should I get?

17:10.570 --> 17:12.990
{\an3}"Reg-u-lar,"
"un-lead-ed"...

17:13.073 --> 17:13.949
{\an3}"Polter"?

17:14.031 --> 17:16.577
Polter gas sounds good.

17:16.660 --> 17:17.618
[bell dings]

17:17.703 --> 17:19.913
[crows cawing]

17:19.997 --> 17:21.790
- [snoring]

17:21.874 --> 17:23.000
- Look, Angry Old Raisin.

17:23.083 --> 17:24.792
I got gas! Mm?

17:24.877 --> 17:27.087
{\an1}- Oh-ho,
fill 'er up, baby.

17:27.171 --> 17:28.630
[gas guzzling]

17:28.714 --> 17:29.798
[scooter banging]

17:29.882 --> 17:30.758
{\an1}[grunting]

17:30.841 --> 17:32.301
Wha--what's happening?

17:32.384 --> 17:33.635
{\an1}Ahh!

17:33.719 --> 17:35.262
{\an1}[yelling]

17:35.345 --> 17:38.474
<i>[ominous music]</i>

17:38.557 --> 17:39.975
[whoosh]

17:40.058 --> 17:41.059
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:41.143 --> 17:42.644
[pinwheel creaking]

17:42.728 --> 17:43.854
Ooh, ooh, ooh.

17:43.937 --> 17:45.397
- Whoa!
[engine rumbling]

17:45.481 --> 17:47.524
{\an3}That polter gas
totally blinged out

17:47.608 --> 17:49.401
your mobility assist device.

17:49.485 --> 17:52.070
- That gas was polter gas?

17:52.154 --> 17:54.156
Oh, no!
[engine revving]

17:54.239 --> 17:55.908
<i>[eerie rock music]</i>

17:55.991 --> 17:59.703
My scooter's out of control
and squashing my tomaters!

17:59.787 --> 18:01.830
- I'll save your tomaters!

18:01.914 --> 18:04.082
[grunting]

18:04.166 --> 18:06.919
- Oh, now my scooter
is squashing you,

18:07.002 --> 18:08.879
which is kind of fun.

18:08.962 --> 18:10.088
[engine revving]
- [grunts]

18:10.172 --> 18:11.340
This hurts my rumpus.

18:11.423 --> 18:12.508
Could you maybe stop?

18:12.591 --> 18:13.509
- Oh, sorry, Pig.

18:13.592 --> 18:15.344
I--I can't control it.

18:15.427 --> 18:17.304
{\an8}- Then I'll save you,
Angry Old Raisin,

18:17.387 --> 18:19.515
{\an8}right after you finish
running me over.

18:19.598 --> 18:20.682
{\an8}[engine revving]

18:20.766 --> 18:22.017
{\an8}Are you done yet?

18:22.100 --> 18:23.352
{\an8}- No, not yet.

18:23.435 --> 18:24.728
{\an8}[engine revving]
Almost.

18:24.812 --> 18:26.063
{\an8}[engine revving]

18:26.146 --> 18:27.439
{\an9}And...

18:27.523 --> 18:30.025
{\an8}[engine revving]
Looks like it's done now.

18:30.108 --> 18:31.068
{\an8}- Phew.

18:31.151 --> 18:32.069
Man, that was cra--

18:32.152 --> 18:33.487
[engine revving]
Ahh!

18:33.570 --> 18:34.780
- I was wrong.

18:34.863 --> 18:36.532
Not done yet.

18:36.615 --> 18:37.908
- Careful, guys.

18:37.991 --> 18:40.410
{\an1}This vase is worth
a hundred bajillion bucks.

18:40.494 --> 18:42.287
- Look out, best friends!

18:42.371 --> 18:43.539
[all grunt]

18:43.622 --> 18:45.707
{\an3}- Phew.
That was a close one.

18:45.791 --> 18:46.708
[vase shatters]

18:46.792 --> 18:47.709
- [panting]

18:47.793 --> 18:49.211
Emergency Rollerblades?

18:49.294 --> 18:50.671
Emergency motorcycle?

18:50.754 --> 18:53.173
Emergency jet-powered
bologna sandwich?

18:53.257 --> 18:54.716
That's the one!

18:54.800 --> 18:55.801
[rockets roaring]

18:55.884 --> 18:57.302
[yells]
[crash]

18:57.386 --> 18:59.763
I'm getting away!
I'm getting away!

18:59.847 --> 19:01.098
Ooh, sandwich.

19:01.181 --> 19:02.224
{\an3}Yum!

19:02.307 --> 19:03.517
[chomps and gulps]

19:03.600 --> 19:05.352
Whoopsie dingles.

19:05.435 --> 19:06.562
Ahh!

19:06.645 --> 19:07.688
[crashing]

19:08.730 --> 19:10.607
Hmm.
[gasps]

19:10.691 --> 19:12.109
I'll save my fourth best friend

19:12.192 --> 19:13.944
by making an eviler lawn mower.

19:14.027 --> 19:15.988
Good thing I still have
some polter gas.

19:16.071 --> 19:16.530
[wolf whistle]

19:16.613 --> 19:19.992
[whooshing]

19:20.075 --> 19:21.702
[crash]

19:21.785 --> 19:22.911
- Wha?

19:22.995 --> 19:24.580
[tires squealing,
engine revving]

19:24.663 --> 19:26.081
- Hi, fourth best friend.

19:26.164 --> 19:27.291
Check it out.

19:27.374 --> 19:28.917
{\an1}- [gasps]
Jumpin' Roosevelts!

19:29.001 --> 19:30.377
A possessed scooter!

19:30.460 --> 19:33.130
- And a totally sweet mower!

19:33.213 --> 19:34.923
- You mow it!

19:35.007 --> 19:37.593
[laughing]

19:37.676 --> 19:38.927
{\an3}Oh-ho-ho!

19:39.011 --> 19:40.095
Whoo!

19:40.178 --> 19:41.638
Hang on, fourth best friend.

19:41.722 --> 19:42.764
I made a monster lawn mower

19:42.848 --> 19:45.726
so I can save
your sweet, wrinkled booty

19:45.809 --> 19:47.227
from your possessed scooty.

19:47.311 --> 19:49.563
- What? I got to get
off of this thing before--

19:49.646 --> 19:51.773
[grunts]
I'm trapped!

19:51.857 --> 19:54.067
I'm old, and I'm trapped!

19:54.151 --> 19:55.152
[seat belts snap]
- Ah!

19:55.235 --> 19:56.695
I'm trapped too!

19:56.778 --> 19:57.696
Help!

19:57.779 --> 19:59.448
[engine roaring]
Ahh!

19:59.531 --> 20:00.908
- Ahh!

20:00.991 --> 20:01.783
- Their monster rides

20:01.867 --> 20:03.493
are gonna crash
into each other!

20:03.577 --> 20:05.078
We need to do something!

20:05.162 --> 20:06.371
- Let me see here.

20:06.455 --> 20:08.457
Possessed scooter
plus monster mower...

20:08.540 --> 20:10.292
[gasps]
That's it! Use the--

20:10.375 --> 20:12.836
- Pig, use the power
of friendship!

20:12.920 --> 20:14.087
- Of course!

20:14.171 --> 20:15.172
Angry Old Raisin,

20:15.255 --> 20:17.257
tell me I'm your best friend.

20:17.341 --> 20:18.884
- [groaning]

20:18.967 --> 20:21.136
You're my best friend!

20:21.219 --> 20:23.138
[engines revving]

20:23.221 --> 20:23.639
- It's not enough!

20:23.722 --> 20:26.308
Say you love me!

20:26.391 --> 20:27.309
- [gags]

20:27.392 --> 20:30.604
I love you!

20:30.687 --> 20:31.480
[engines revving]

20:31.563 --> 20:33.482
[chomp]

20:33.565 --> 20:35.359
- It's still not enough!

20:35.442 --> 20:36.610
Quick, ask me to marry you!

20:36.693 --> 20:39.071
- Wha--ahh!

20:39.154 --> 20:41.031
Ohh!

20:41.114 --> 20:45.953
Pig, will you marry me?

20:46.036 --> 20:46.954
[engines revving]

20:47.037 --> 20:50.290
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

20:50.374 --> 20:52.501
[engines revving]

20:52.584 --> 20:53.835
- This is really sudden!

20:53.919 --> 20:55.462
You're moving too fast!

20:55.545 --> 20:59.341
{\an1}- You just told me to ask,
you goofy turkey!

20:59.424 --> 21:02.052
{\an3}- Okay, fine,
I'll marry you!

21:02.135 --> 21:04.054
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:04.137 --> 21:06.556
[whirring]

21:06.640 --> 21:08.141
[explosion booms]
Ah!

21:08.225 --> 21:10.477
[both grunting]

21:10.560 --> 21:12.104
[thud]

21:12.187 --> 21:14.856
{\an1}- Do we really have
to get married?

21:14.940 --> 21:17.484
{\an3}- Yes, yes, you have
to get married,

21:17.567 --> 21:19.361
{\an3}because that's
what happens

21:19.444 --> 21:22.322
in the Goofy Turkey Zone!

21:22.406 --> 21:23.532
- [guffaws]

21:23.615 --> 21:25.450
That guy looks
like Banana.

21:25.534 --> 21:27.452
- Hold on now.

21:27.536 --> 21:28.954
He was in my lab
before I went

21:29.037 --> 21:31.331
{\an3}on a million time travel
dates with Goat.

21:31.415 --> 21:32.499
[chuckling nervously]

21:32.582 --> 21:33.875
{\an3}Uh, no, that never
happened.

21:33.959 --> 21:34.876
[laughs and snorts]

21:34.960 --> 21:36.003
- And he was by my window

21:36.086 --> 21:39.214
{\an1}before Gorf Gorfed me
with that Gorfing kazoo!

21:39.298 --> 21:42.384
- And he was in my video game!

21:42.467 --> 21:44.386
all: Get him!

21:44.469 --> 21:46.304
- [grunting]

21:46.388 --> 21:48.140
[panting]

21:48.223 --> 21:49.266
[door bangs]

21:49.349 --> 21:50.726
[all grunting]

21:50.809 --> 21:52.060
- Uh, hey, guys,

21:52.144 --> 21:53.437
how do we get out of here?

21:53.520 --> 21:54.563
[bongo flourish]

21:54.646 --> 21:55.939
all: Pig Goat Banana Cricket

21:56.023 --> 21:58.066
we're stuck
in the Goofy Turkey Zone

21:58.150 --> 21:59.234
high five!

21:59.317 --> 22:00.569
<i>[dramatic musical flourish]</i>

22:02.821 --> 22:05.574
{\an8}[gentle acoustic guitar music]

22:05.657 --> 22:12.664
{\an8}♪ ♪

22:25.844 --> 22:27.554
{\an8}[whoopee cushion whistles]
